## Vercel Web Analytics Installation - Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

### Changes Made

**1. Package Installation**
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^1.6.1` using pnpm
- Package added to dependencies in `package.json`
- Generated `pnpm-lock.yaml` lockfile for dependency consistency

**2. Root Layout Configuration (src/app/layout.tsx)**
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- Placed `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag after `{children}`
- Maintains existing code structure and styling

**3. Verification Steps Completed**
- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ Linter verified - no new errors introduced in layout.tsx
- ✅ All files staged with git (package.json, src/app/layout.tsx, pnpm-lock.yaml)

### Implementation Details

The Analytics component has been added to the root layout following Next.js App Router best practices:
- Positioned after `{children}` in the body tag for proper page load tracking
- Will automatically track page views and web vitals
- No additional configuration needed - analytics will work once deployed to Vercel

### Files Modified

1. **web/package.json** - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
2. **web/src/app/layout.tsx** - Imported and added Analytics component
3. **web/pnpm-lock.yaml** - New lockfile generated by pnpm

### Notes

- The project uses Next.js 16.1.0 with App Router (app directory structure)
- Package manager: pnpm
- Analytics component is correctly placed and will start tracking once deployed to Vercel
- Pre-existing linting errors in other components (Search.tsx, SearchPageClient.tsx) were not addressed as they are unrelated to this implementation
